   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>V. THE MIGHTY MEN OF DAVID</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>Verses 8 through 39 speak of the mighty men of David.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>A. The First Three Mighty Men</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>The first three mighty men were Josheb-basshebeth, the chief of the captains, Eleazar, and Shammah vv.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>8-12 .</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>B. The Second Three Mighty Men,</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>Who Drew the Water</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>from the Well of Bethlehem for David</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>The second three mighty men were those who drew water from the well of Bethlehem for David vv.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>13-23 .</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>Abishai, the chief of the three and the most honored among the thirty, became their leader, but he did not attain to the first three vv.</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>18-19 .</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>Benaiah, more honored than the thirty but not attaining to the first three, was set by David over his guard vv.</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>20-23 .</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>C. The Thirty Mighty Men</S>
   <S PAR='16' RSNT='1' SNO='16'>Verses 24 through 39 give the names of the thirty mighty men.</S>
   <S PAR='17' RSNT='1' SNO='17'>One of the thirty was Uriah, who was killed by David's conspiracy.</S>
   <S PAR='18' RSNT='1' SNO='18'>VI.</S>
   <S PAR='19' RSNT='1' SNO='19'>THE LAST SIN OF DAVID</S>
   <S PAR='20' RSNT='1' SNO='20'>In chapter twenty-four and in 1 Chronicles 21 we have an account of the last sin of David.</S>
   <S PAR='21' RSNT='1' SNO='21'>A. The Anger of Jehovah against Israel</S>
   <S PAR='22' RSNT='1' SNO='22'>Again the anger of Jehovah was kindled against Israel 2 Sam 24:1a .</S>
   <S PAR='23' RSNT='1' SNO='23'>B. Satan's Moving David against Israel</S>
   <S PAR='24' RSNT='1' SNO='24'>to Number Israel and Judah</S>
   <S PAR='25' RSNT='1' SNO='25'>Satan moved David against Israel to number Israel and Judah vv.</S>
   <S PAR='26' RSNT='1' SNO='26'>1b-2; 1 Chron 21:1 .</S>
   <S PAR='27' RSNT='1' SNO='27'>Satan's moving David to do this was permitted by God.</S>
   <S PAR='28' RSNT='1' SNO='28'>C. Joab's Disagreement with Numbering the People</S>
   <S PAR='29' RSNT='1' SNO='29'>Joab disagreed with numbering the people and said to David, "Now may Jehovah your God add to the people a hundred times as many as they are, while the eyes of my lord the king may see it.</S>
   <S PAR='30' RSNT='1' SNO='30'>But why does my lord the king desire this thing?"</S>
   <S PAR='31' RSNT='1' SNO='31'>2 Sam 24:3 .</S>
   </TEXT>
